The nicest thing about it being in HTML5 is that messing with it&#x27;s variables it&#x27;s really easy. To make it harder, you can (for example), load the page, open the developer console, type<p>ZType.WAVES = {EXPERT: {
            wave: 0,
            spawn: [],
            spawnWait: 0.3,
            healthBoost: 0,
            types: [{
                type: EntityEnemyOppressor,
                count: 3,
                incEvery: 4
            }, {
                type: EntityEnemyDestroyer,
                count: 5,
                incEvery: 2
            }, {
                type: EntityEnemyMine,
                count: 10,
                incEvery: 1
            }]
        }
}<p>And then start a game on expert mode.<p>You can mess up with the values to make it harder/easier.
